This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computer Science - Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with Fully Homomorphic Encryption (FHE) and its potential to address data privacy issues in medical image classification tasks. Additionally, the paper also involves Computer Vision (cs.CV) as it applies CNNs to medical image classification tasks. The paper also involves Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new FHE compact packing scheme that is tightly integrated with CNN functions. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is also a likely category as the paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques to medical imaging. Finally, Cybersecurity (cs.CY) is also a possible category as the paper deals with secure deep learning inference in clinical imaging.
